            "body": "I updated that piece and pushed again. Because the failure count was so high, I put it through AI to sort through it a bit more, and it came back with this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n• Problem statement: setting fillchars=eob:~ in test/functional/testnvim.lua is both invasive and incomplete. It changes option\r\n  metadata, but many failing tests use raw child sessions that bypass that default anyway.\r\n\r\n  Relevant examples:\r\n\r\n  - test/functional/testnvim.lua:27-31\r\n    Default harness settings. Adding fillchars=eob:~ here makes fillchars look user-set, which breaks option metadata tests.\r\n  - test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua:3787\r\n    This test intentionally sets fillchars from a sourced file and expects that source location to be reported.\r\n  - test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua:3814-3852\r\n    These assertions check last_set_linenr / last_set_sid. A harness-level set fillchars=... pollutes those values.\r\n  - test/functional/ui/screen_basic_spec.lua:14-30\r\n    This test creates its own argv with merge = false, so it bypasses testnvim.lua defaults entirely.\r\n  - test/functional/ui/screen_basic_spec.lua:34-39\r\n    Old fixture expects ~, but raw session renders the new default ·.\r\n  - test/functional/ui/screen.lua:68-71\r\n    Proposed compatibility point: normalize actual highlighted default EOB · rows to ~ for old fixtures.\r\n  - test/functional/ui/screen.lua:632-653\r\n    Central comparison path where that normalization lets old screen expectations pass without changing Nvim option state.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAre we sure we don't just want to update the test expectations and call it a day? It's file churn, but it should be fairly dumb file churn that either passes or doesn't. Even if half the list above is hallucinated, that's a fair amount of blast radius that actually breaks many test assumptions throughout the `functionaltest` suite.\r\n\r\n(If I'm missing something and there is an easier solution here, please let me know. I'm not an expert on this codebase yet.)",
